A Stanford study which examined earnings among over a million rideshare drivers on Uber shows that male drivers earn 7% more than females. The reasons for this “gender pay gap” among Uber drivers were: The researchers said their study shows that “women’s relatively high opportunity cost of non-paid-work time and gender-based preference differences can perpetuate a gender earnings gap even in the absence of discrimination”. The full study is available here: The Gender Earnings Gap in the Gig Economy